title: Parker has triple-double, US women win in Spain
text:
Parker has triple-double, US women win in Spain - Wandtv.com, NewsCenter17, StormCenter17, Central Illinois News- Member Center: Parker has triple-double, US women win in Spain Posted: Updated: 
GIRONA, Spain (AP) - Candace Parker had a triple-double with 14 points, 12 assists and 10 rebounds to help the U.S. women's team open its European tour with a 94-52 victory over Uni Girona on Sunday night. 
The Los Angeles Sparks star was 7 of 11 from the field and had three steals and two blocks. 
Elena Delle Donne of the Chicago Sky had 21 points in her first game for the national team. 
The Americans will face Italy in Rome on Wednesday night, Dike Naples on Thursday night in Italy, and finish the tour Friday night at EuroLeague champion USK Prague. 
Uni Girona won the Spanish League title last season.
